{{notability|Products|date=February 2016}} {{primary sources|date=February 2016}} '''Automatic Tracking Satellite Dishes''' are [[satellite dish]]es used while a vehicle is in motion. Automatic tracking satellite dishes utilize [[gyroscopes]], [[GPS]] position sensors, and uses unique satellite identification data and an integrated [[Digital Video Broadcasting|DVB]] decoder to aid in identification of the satellite that it is pointing at.
The dishes consist usually of [[stepper motor]]s to drive and aim the dish, [[gyroscopes]] to detect changes in position while the vehicle is in motion, a [[parabolic reflector]], [[low-noise block converter]], and control unit.
== Manufacturers == * Winegard Company<ref>[http://www.winegard.com Winegard Company]</ref> * KVH Industries * Sea Tel * Orbit Technology Group<ref>[http://www.orbit-techgroup.com/ Orbit Technology Group]</ref> * Ten-Haaft<ref>[http://www.ten-haaft.de Ten-Haaft]</ref>
